00:11:50.190 --> 00:11:51.490
&gt;&gt; Dawn Lundy Martin: Untethered

00:11:51.490 --> 00:11:55.860
from happenings rooted
to temporality.

00:11:55.860 --> 00:12:00.120
Untethered from happenings
rooted to temporality.

00:12:00.120 --> 00:12:04.990
The I is made of many
arches and windows.

00:12:04.990 --> 00:12:12.330
Enter this structure, the entrances
into the many houses of God and

00:12:12.330 --> 00:12:19.040
yet each morning a fireheart
grief coming out of sleep,

00:12:19.040 --> 00:12:25.300
the listening to the smoke as it
fills and weeps inside the chest,

00:12:25.300 --> 00:12:31.560
choking strength out,
hands weighted, dangling.

00:12:31.560 --> 00:12:37.540
We wonder where else it
lives before it fills us up.

00:12:37.540 --> 00:12:44.290
We assume it comes inside through
the hole that promises invasion.

00:12:44.290 --> 00:12:49.190
This layering of forms pushes
you toward abstraction.

00:12:49.190 --> 00:12:52.750
We have stolen madness
from the White people.

00:12:52.750 --> 00:12:58.320
An angry white man will call
us a crazy bitch in a text.

00:12:58.320 --> 00:13:00.910
But we have long done been free.

00:13:00.910 --> 00:13:05.340
Coffee is brought to our
bedside on a silver tray.

00:13:05.340 --> 00:13:07.520
We are un-representable.

00:13:07.520 --> 00:13:10.080
We sip into the grief mouth.

00:13:11.130 --> 00:13:13.770
&gt;&gt; Ron Charles: Thank you.

00:13:13.770 --> 00:13:18.770
The I is made of many
arches and windows.

00:13:18.770 --> 00:13:27.180 position:56%
Such a paradox to think of ourselves
as being portals, as being parts

00:13:27.180 --> 00:13:30.330
of architecture and
then you conclude

00:13:30.330 --> 00:13:33.420
by saying we are un-representable
even

00:13:33.420 --> 00:13:34.950
as you try and represent yourself.

00:13:34.950 --> 00:13:36.550
That is sort of a paradox
you through again

00:13:36.550 --> 00:13:37.850
